article.description: Scottie James had 15 points as Liberty beat Stetson 71-53 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: James scores 15 to carry Liberty over Stetson 71-53
article.linkText: James scores 15 to carry Liberty over Stetson 71-53
article.story: DELAND, Fla. -- Scottie James had 15 points as Liberty beat Stetson 71-53 on Wednesday night. Darius McGhee had eight rebounds for Liberty (13-4, 2-0 Atlantic Sun Conference). Lovell Cabbil added seven rebounds. The Hatters' 17 points in the first half marked a season low for the team. Christiaan Jones had 12 points for the Hatters (4-12, 0-1). Jahlil Rawley added six assists. Liberty matches up against Jacksonville (7-9, 0-1) at home on Saturday. Stetson takes on Lipscomb (10-4, 1-0) on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
